- Hey.
- Hey.

01:10.001 --> 01:12.169
What do you think
of this tie?

01:12.203 --> 01:13.904
I think...

01:13.938 --> 01:17.140
I want to
tie you up with it.

01:17.174 --> 01:23.046
Really?
And what brought that on?

01:23.080 --> 01:25.515
Okay, well,

01:25.550 --> 01:28.718
then let's make

01:28.753 --> 01:31.855
that happen.

01:31.889 --> 01:33.323
Wait.

01:33.357 --> 01:34.524
Is this to do things
to me

01:34.559 --> 01:36.125
or just to get control
of the remote?

01:36.160 --> 01:37.761
Why can't it be both?

01:37.795 --> 01:40.463
Rachel, if you think I'm gonna
let you watch <i>Game of Thrones</i>

01:40.497 --> 01:42.030
while sexually dominating me,

01:42.065 --> 01:45.067
then you are absolutely right.

01:47.604 --> 01:50.706
Seriously, what's got you
feeling so good?

01:50.740 --> 01:52.140
Oh, it just feels like
such a weight off

01:52.175 --> 01:53.408
now that Louis doesn't--

01:53.443 --> 01:55.077
- Despise me?
- Mm-hmm.

01:55.111 --> 01:57.179
Ah, you know what else
would feel like a weight off?

01:59.649 --> 02:01.684
- Oh--
- No. No, no, no.

02:01.718 --> 02:03.519
Nobody ever calls
the landline except my parents.

02:03.553 --> 02:05.187
- What if something's wrong?
- It's fine.

02:05.221 --> 02:06.221
Mike.

02:06.255 --> 02:08.590
Okay, okay, okay.

02:08.624 --> 02:09.991
Hello.

02:10.026 --> 02:11.994
Yeah, this is him.

02:14.630 --> 02:17.199
Yeah, of course
I can come meet you.

02:17.233 --> 02:20.469
Can I ask what this is--
hello?

02:20.503 --> 02:21.536
Who was it?

02:21.570 --> 02:23.005
Professor Gerard.

02:23.039 --> 02:24.572
He wants me to go meet him.

02:24.607 --> 02:25.807
Did he say
what it was about?

02:25.841 --> 02:27.442
No, he hung up.

02:27.477 --> 02:29.044
When does he want you
to meet him?

02:29.078 --> 02:30.212
Right now.

02:32.615 --> 02:36.884
- Professor Gerard.
- Thanks for coming.

02:36.918 --> 02:38.819
I wouldn't have bothered you
if it wasn't important.

02:38.853 --> 02:40.854
It's not a problem.
What can I help you with?

02:40.889 --> 02:42.623
It's not me.

02:42.657 --> 02:45.993
A former employee at
Liberty Rail reached out to me.

02:46.028 --> 02:47.594
He claims he was fired
because he knows

02:47.629 --> 02:49.430
the real reason
for the crash.

02:49.464 --> 02:52.333
And what was
the real reason?

02:52.367 --> 02:53.700
He wouldn't tell me.

02:53.735 --> 02:54.902
Well, what did he
tell you?

02:54.936 --> 02:57.138
Enough for me to know
it would be unethical

02:57.172 --> 03:00.541
if somebody didn't
look into this.

03:00.575 --> 03:03.744
But you can't, so you want me
to get Harvey to.

03:03.778 --> 03:06.013
Well, you convinced him
to look into my case

03:06.048 --> 03:07.248
when he didn't want to,
didn't you?

03:07.282 --> 03:09.616
This is different.
We don't take cases like this.

03:09.651 --> 03:12.653
Maybe,

03:12.687 --> 03:15.622
but I believe a man
who can convince Harvey

03:15.657 --> 03:17.490
to hire someone
who never went to law school

03:17.525 --> 03:20.360
could convince him
to make an exception for this.

03:22.329 --> 03:25.032
What?

03:25.066 --> 03:26.900
He didn't tell you I know.

03:29.437 --> 03:30.671
No, he didn't.

03:30.705 --> 03:33.006
Well, I do.

03:34.909 --> 03:38.812
But what I'm asking you to do
and me knowing

03:38.846 --> 03:40.980
have nothing
to do with each other.

03:43.750 --> 03:45.184
I appreciate that.

03:45.218 --> 03:48.287
Does that mean that you're
gonna tell him to take the case?

03:48.321 --> 03:49.889
I have a better idea.

03:55.428 --> 03:56.963
Got a second?

03:56.997 --> 03:59.231
Of course.
What do you need?

03:59.265 --> 04:02.068
I'd like you to sign off
on my vacation request.

04:04.404 --> 04:06.138
Paris.

04:06.172 --> 04:07.739
I've never heard you
talk about Paris.

04:07.773 --> 04:11.176
No, but I have heard you
talk about it,

04:11.211 --> 04:13.178
which is why I'm taking you.

04:14.380 --> 04:16.748
Are you asking me
to go to Paris with you?

04:16.781 --> 04:18.016
I believe I just did.

04:18.050 --> 04:19.089
Jeff, do you have any idea

04:19.119 --> 04:20.519
how much is on my plate
right now?

04:20.553 --> 04:21.685
Actually, I do, all of which

04:21.721 --> 04:24.022
Harvey has agreed to cover.

04:24.056 --> 04:25.924
You went to Harvey with this.

04:25.958 --> 04:27.359
Well, I would have
come to you first,

04:27.393 --> 04:30.262
but then it really
wouldn't be a surprise.

04:32.664 --> 04:34.232
I'll think about it.

04:34.266 --> 04:36.334
Take all the time you need.

04:36.368 --> 04:37.701
But in the meantime,

04:37.736 --> 04:40.671
I'll be thinking about
who else around here I can take.

04:40.705 --> 04:42.240
Really?

04:42.274 --> 04:44.408
Well, you're awfully
sure of yourself.

04:44.443 --> 04:47.011
You think I haven't seen
the way Norma looks at me?

04:47.045 --> 04:48.912
Calls me
the Black Stallion.

04:55.253 --> 04:57.054
Norma.

05:00.291 --> 05:01.291
Taking a case.

05:01.325 --> 05:02.693
What kind of case?

05:02.727 --> 05:03.994
What does it matter?

05:04.029 --> 05:05.896
Because you wouldn't be
announcing it like that

05:05.930 --> 05:07.364
if there wasn't something wrong.

05:07.398 --> 05:10.367
It's a case that came
from Professor Gerard.

05:10.401 --> 05:11.468
What?

05:11.502 --> 05:12.736
A man who used to work
at Liberty Rail

05:12.771 --> 05:14.771
says the real cause
of the crash was covered up.

05:14.805 --> 05:16.072
Then refer him to a firm

05:16.106 --> 05:17.840
that takes whistle-blower cases,
because we don't.

05:17.875 --> 05:18.941
Yeah, I'm not gonna do that.

05:18.976 --> 05:20.476
Then don't,
but there's a reason

05:20.510 --> 05:22.812
lawyers who take whistle-blower
cases don't work here,

05:22.846 --> 05:24.313
and it's because corporations

05:24.347 --> 05:26.082
don't appreciate
shakedown artists.

05:26.116 --> 05:27.476
And what if
this isn't a shakedown?

05:27.484 --> 05:28.617
And how do you know
it isn't?

05:28.652 --> 05:30.252
What I know is that
innocent people died--

05:30.287 --> 05:32.789
mothers and fathers
and sons and daughters--

05:32.823 --> 05:35.158
and if somebody's covering up
why that happened

05:35.192 --> 05:36.726
and I can stop it,
then I'm going to.

05:36.760 --> 05:38.127
And I said you're not.

05:38.162 --> 05:40.029
Well, but you also said
that Professor Gerard

05:40.064 --> 05:41.864
didn't know my secret.

05:43.232 --> 05:45.500
Harvey, I know,
I know he'll never tell anyone,

05:45.534 --> 05:47.703
but someday, someone's
gonna find out who will,

05:47.737 --> 05:48.737
and I'll be done.

05:48.738 --> 05:49.771
Mike, he's not--

05:49.806 --> 05:51.506
Harvey, I got
into this whole thing

05:51.540 --> 05:54.810
so that I could try
to help people,

05:54.844 --> 05:56.544
and I don't know
how much time I have left,

05:56.579 --> 06:00.749
so please,

06:00.783 --> 06:03.785
let me try
and help these people.

06:07.556 --> 06:09.124
Then you better make damn sure

06:09.158 --> 06:12.159
this whistle-blower
isn't full of sh--.

06:17.666 --> 06:21.102
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

06:21.136 --> 06:24.572
♪ Get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:24.607 --> 06:27.742
♪ Everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:27.776 --> 06:31.278
♪ Everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:31.312 --> 06:34.414
♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,
I don't mind ♪

06:34.449 --> 06:38.418
♪ Me and Missy is
so busy, busy making money ♪

06:38.453 --> 06:39.886
♪ All right

06:39.887 --> 06:41.458
